Bluetongue, Egypt
-----------------
Information received 11 Mar 2019 from Dr Mahmoud Mohamed Ali Abdelhakim, chief researcher, CVO and chairman, General Organization for Veterinary Services (GOVS), Ministry of Agriculture and Land Reclamation, Giza, Egypt

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 30 Aug 2018
Date of confirmation of the event: 6 Mar 2019
Report date: 10 Mar 2019
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 1974
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: 4
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak location: Wadi Elnatron, Al Buhayrah
Date of start of the outbreak: 30 Aug 2018
Outbreak status: resolved 26 Nov 2018
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 484 / 70 / 35 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 14 / 7 / 50 / 7
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; screening; traceability; quarantine; official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste; zoning; disinfection; control of vectors; vector surveillance; vaccination prohibited; no treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Animal Health Research Institute (National laboratory) / Cattle / real-time PCR / 20 Sep 2018 / Positive
The Pirbright Institute, United Kingdom (OIE Reference Laboratory) / Cattle / real-time PCR / 6 Mar 2019 / Positive
The Pirbright Institute, United Kingdom (OIE Reference Laboratory) / Cattle / serotyping / 6 Mar 2019 / Positive

Future Reporting: the event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

